    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-10-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="636"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 847/142.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign Affairs of
                            Panama</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Profoundly thankful for your excellency’s felicitations. I avail myself of the
                    opportunity to express my hope that the relations of our two countries may ever
                    be as close and cordial as they have been heretofore.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arango.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
